# Windows shell (Command Prompt)

When running terminal commands in this repo on Windows:

- Use **Command Prompt** (`cmd.exe`), not PowerShell.
- Chain with `&&`, not `;`.
- Use `set VAR=value` for env vars, not `$env:VAR`.
- Prefer `cmd /c "..."` when a single wrapped command is clearer.
- Avoid PowerShell-only syntax (`$()`, backtick line continuation, `New-Item`, `Out-Null`).

Example:

```bat
cmd /c "cd /d \"c:\Work\Side Projects\agent-gate\" && pnpm test"
```

Only use PowerShell when the user explicitly asks for it or a task requires PowerShell-only tooling.
